# Stop the Node Service

First, stop the running service safely:
```
sudo systemctl stop republicd
```
# Navigate to the Cosmovisor Genesis Binary Directory
```
cd $HOME/.republicd/cosmovisor/genesis/bin
```
# Download the New Binary (v0.2.0)

Fetch the latest binary from the official repository:
```
wget -O republicd_v2 https://github.com/RepublicAI/networks/releases/download/v0.2.0/republicd-linux-amd64
```
# Verify Binary Integrity (SHA256)

Validate the checksum to ensure file integrity:
```
echo "0788832a9f88fedfe1e2896391dd4bdb944aca85ae0632f3d30e09743a455b65  republicd_v2" | sha256sum -c
```

Expected output:

OK

# Grant Execute Permission
```
chmod +x republicd_v2
```
# Backup Old Binary & Activate the New One

Create a backup of the previous version before replacing it:
```
mv republicd republicd_v0.1.0_backup
mv republicd_v2 republicd
```

 Keep the backup in case a rollback is required.

# Restart the Node Service
```
sudo systemctl daemon-reload
sudo systemctl enable republicd
sudo systemctl start republicd
```
# Monitor Logs

Check logs to ensure the node starts correctly and resumes syncing:
```
sudo journalctl -u republicd -f
```

If block height progresses and matches the explorer, the update is successful.

# Optional: Version Check
```
republicd version
```

Expected output:

v0.2.0
